Support caller-driven tool calling (return calls; replay tool history + Gemini 3
thought signatures).

drupal/gemini_provider 1.0.1's GeminiProvider is incompatible with any caller
that owns its own tool loop (FlowDrop's reason node, ai_agents). Three problems:

1. chat() EXECUTED every function call in-provider: handleFunctionCall() resolved
   the tool NAME against the AI FunctionCall registry
   (getFunctionCallFromFunctionName(), keyed by function_name) and ran it, folding
   the output into the reply text. FlowDrop names a tool from its node LABEL
   ("Capability: Studio tour" -> "capability_studio_tour"), which is not a
   registered function_name, so the lookup threw "Function with name
   capability_studio_tour not found." and the reason node / StateGraph run failed.
   Even on a hit it bypassed the caller's invoker/allow-list/audit and never put
   the call on the ChatMessage. Fix: extractFunctionCall() returns each call as a
   ToolsFunctionOutput on the message (setTools()), like the other providers.
   Gemini emits no tool-call id, so synthesize a unique non-empty one (FlowDrop's
   ToolPairing drops id-less calls).

2. The payload builder only handled text/images and threw "The role tool, is not
   supported by Gemini Provider." on the tool-result turn the caller appends after
   running a tool -- so the NEXT reason turn died. Fix: replay history as Gemini's
   function-calling graph -- an assistant turn with tool calls becomes a model
   Content of functionCall parts, and the tool-result turns become one user
   Content of functionResponse parts (paired back to the call name via the
   id->name map, since a tool-result turn carries only the id). Also resets the
   per-message parts buffer (it previously accumulated across messages).

3. Gemini 3 rejects a replayed functionCall that is missing the model's
   thought_signature ("Function call is missing a thought_signature..."), but the
   only tool-call data that survives a caller's round-trip is {name, args,
   tool_call_id} -- the signature is dropped. Fix: stash the signature in an
   expirable keyvalue store keyed by the synthesized tool id when the call is
   returned, and restore it onto the Part when the call is replayed.

